    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's what your $5 million contribution in 10 years would be worth in today's dollars:\n\n| Discount Rate | Present Value |\n|---------------|---------------|\n| **4%** | $3.38M |\n| **6%** | $2.79M |\n| **8%** | $2.32M |\n| **10%** | $1.93M |\n\n**What this means:**\n\n- At a **4% discount rate**, you'd need to set aside about $3.4 million today to have $5 million available in 10 years.\n- At **6%**, the present value drops to $2.8 million—you'd need less capital now because your funds have more time to grow.\n- At **8%**, it's about $2.3 million.\n- At **10%**, it's roughly $1.9 million.\n\nThe appropriate discount rate depends on your expected investment return between now and then. If you expect to earn 6% annually on funds set aside, using a 6% discount rate shows the true cost in today's dollars.\n\nWould you like me to run any additional scenarios, such as comparing present values across different time horizons (e.g., contributing in 15 or 20 years instead of 10)?"
